subject: Squash (Sport)
lead_paragraph: Karim Darwish of Egypt became the world’s new No. 1 player, ending the 33-month reign of his compatriot Amr Shabana. Darwish, 27, from Cairo, is the 13th player to top the men’s world list, but only the second Egyptian. Darwish, a former junior world champion, was eighth in the rankings at the start of 2008, but he reached six finals — including the World Open in October — and won three titles, including his first Super Series crowns in Qatar and Saudi Arabia. Shabana slipped to No. 2, and the World Open champion Ramy Ashour remained at No. 3.
